Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.95,0:08:21.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,800)\c&H00FFFF&}以下是Techmoan在介绍区的Q&A节选
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:27.96,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,47)}问：我能用这个看到软盘上的磁信号吗？\NA) 不行:-( 我试验了5.25吋的软盘，两面都没有:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:27.96,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,933)\fnComic Sans MS\fs55}Q) CAN IT SEE WHATS ON A FLOPPY DISK?\NA) No - It didn’t show anything on a 5.25” floppy I tested (BOTH SIDES)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:33.60,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,47)}Q) 你可以买些磁性观察纸来做这些事啊 \NA) 它们的敏感度不一样......至少我买到的不行。它们不能显示磁带上的信号。\N我试了好几遍都没有:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:33.60,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs55\pos(990,873)}Q) You can buy these sheets of magnetic viewing paper that do the same thing. \NA) They don’t have the same resolution or sensitivity - at least the ones I’ve bought don’t. They can’t show the magnetic signal and track layout on a tape. Nothing registered when I tried. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:42.04,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs55\pos(965,750)}Q) You can use this fluid stuff that does the same job\NA) A few people are mentioning various ways to do this with a liquid smeared on the tape. These were known about, and likely made, by 3M as well. But one reason for the development of the magnetic tape viewer was that it was a ‘non destructive’ way to read the tape. Here’s an except from their patent application where they mention one of the existing and alternative methods to do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:42.04,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,47)}Q) 你可以自己做这种流体来看嘛\NA) 有人确实提过很多方法来将液体涂抹到磁带上来看磁性分布，3M知道这个方法\N而且3M可能也试过这个东西，但是开发磁带查看器的原因之一是，它可以无伤读取磁带磁性分布。\N他们在专利申请中提到过，而且也提出了很多方法来做这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:47.54,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs55\pos(960,146)}Q) Who is the voice in the Datsun Commercial?  \NA) Danny Dark
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:47.54,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,41)}Q) 那个广告是谁配的音？ \NA) Danny Dark
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:47.54,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\pos(964,814)}Q) 盒子左边的白色平台是干啥的? \NA) 那是个观察板，想要仔细看的话，请空降2:51
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:47.54,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs55\pos(990,917)}Q) What’s the white pad on the left for. \NA) Thats the ‘Viewing Pad’ - to see a picture of it being used - freeze the video at 02:51
